rComments: The best professor in the Telfer MBA program, hands down. She is inspirational, understands pedagogy, and a leader in her field. Highly recommend taking any of her classes!

Incredible professor. She made what could be very boring content, extremely interesting. Prof. Mazutis only tests broad concepts, show up to class and pay attention and you will ace her class. Favourite first year prof at Telfer

She was the best prof I had in first year at Telfer. I highly recommend taking her class! She made the material interesting and engaging, and she is an amazing lecturer. Study her slides and you will do well; the textbook is not needed.
She's a very nice prof who's really passionate about her class. She makes the course content interesting and the weekly assignments help out your mark a lot. Recommended.

Definitely my favourite prof at UO. She made the content of the course both interesting and relevant to daily life. Weekly assignments allow for a basically free 10% of final grade. Lectures are interesting and don't just follow the textbook. She made every class enjoyable and I would definitely recommend her as a prof for 1301 or any other course
Very passionate. Group project was a bit annoying.
Favorite prof!

Professor Mazutis was one of my favourite first year business profs at U of O. For the midterm and exam, only broad concepts are really covered so as long as you attend class and understand everything that is discussed, you will only need to study a minimal amount. She applies all lecture concepts to the real world, with lots of discussion.

Great prof and interesting lectures! I highly recommend going to each class since you'll absorb so much information. Honestly you don't even need the textbook, just go to class, listen, and take notes. Midterm and final are easy to ace as long as you've been paying attention all semester. I did minimal skimming of slides as revision.

She really is a great prof. She manages to make extremely dry subject matter very interesting. She really changed my perspective on the international business environment. I would highly recommend her.
Best teacher I've ever had to date. Loved the interactive lecture style. Super intelligent and friendly, if you go to class and participate, you'll do great.
She's a great prof. Makes a really boring course quit interesting with her teaching style. This course changed my perspective in business.

Prof. Mazutis was very inspirational. Her lectures made me feel that I can truly make a difference in the world. Her midterm and final were fair, and you get a free 10% if you do these weekly assignments. However, do not pack up to leave before the lecture officially ends, and pay full attention to videos she shows - those are her pet peeves.

It wasn't Mazutis' fault that the course content just sucked in general, but she did just a horrible,horrible job of presenting it. Her lectures were boring and dry and anytime actual import info was put on a slide she moved so fast you couldn't even copy the notes on them. Also things from dumb videos in class showed up on midterm without warning!

I feel that Daina would benefit from a more exciting curriculum. She took a seemingly boring class and made it relatively enjoyable. Her lectures were very original, not straight from the textbook. She is a great speaker and teacher. The material isn't difficult, but it isn't very interesting, and she made me enjoy it much more than expected

Funny teacher who understands how difficult it is for first year students. She encourages discussion and her midterms were relatively  easy. I wish she would actually post all the lectures ahead of time and she does a chapter per class which is hard compared to other profs who do 1 chapter for 2 classes so u learn it better. Also gives easy 10%.
Amazing prof. Makes the class interesting and is an easy grader. As long as you pay attention to the slides in class, you'll be okay.

My favourite prof so far. Very clear rubrics, very approachable. Makes herself available if you have any questions. Lectures are engaging and she encourages discussion in class. Does't teach directly from the textbook, so the lectures are more engaging.

My favourite prof of my University career so far! She is always engaging and gives valuable feedback. She always makes herself available for questions and is very approachable.  Lots of group projects and group sessions in class.

Amazing professor. She engages the class in discussion and she seems genuinely interested in what students have to say. Her explanations are very clear and easy to understand. This class is also an easy A.
Daina is a better than average prof. Well prepared with good knowledge of business but a little too high on herself. Listening to her you will learn about the real world.

Best professor ever. Previously taken adm1301 and dropped it. Very thankful I had the opportunity to learn from her. Very knowledgeable and passionate. Would definitely recommend. Gives clear instructions for group work !
As most said, very passionate and as long as you know what she's passionate about, you'll know what the write for the tests. Very fair marker.

I really liked Prof Mazutis! She is a really nice lady and a great teacher. She is obviously passionate about the subject and she knows what she's talking about. You don't need to take notes and as long as you pay attention in class you can do well on her exams!

Apparently before she came to the school, a pretty strict prof was teaching the course (so we should all be glad that she's here because she's pretty easy.) She has this really friendly aura even though she looks intimidating, and she's definitely passionate about the course.  I'm pretty sure if you show up and listen, you'd pass.

Don't worry about taking notes, Professor Mazutis doesn't care for details and memorization. Just absorb the classroom experiences and you'll do fine on the tests. Overall, she is a great Prof. Good sense of humour too.

She's a great professor. 10% of your mark is earned by just doing simple weekly assignments. (some of them were just surveys and cool racism/sexism spectrum tests) I don't think you'll need her book, but you definitely don't want to miss out on her lessons. I have her exam this Saturday, so no comment on that lol

You just WANT to listen to her because she's SOO passionate about the course. You can tell that she knows her stuff, because she's worked with so many corporations. The stuff we learn is really eye opening too. Her tests are pretty easy, and you're good if you'd just read her slides. I would totally take another class with Dr. Mazutis!

Her midterm was decent, but she is a really easy marker. I love her class because you can actually learn a lot and she's really passionate. I don't think I've ever been bored in the class, and i love group discussions!! She's so open minded and i really like her teaching style. Wanted to rate her for so long but her name never showed up until now!

Prof. Mazutis is very passionate about her teaching and that is a big factor in helping students learn. To better understand the subjects we would go through Case Studies which I found very helpful. While it's not an "easy A" minimal studying and attending class can get you an A.
